 been defined by\nthe collective evolution of a system-wide cooperation of polymer aggregates.\nOverall, the results presented demonstrate the merits of considering plausible\nprebiotic polymer chemistries and environments that would have allowed for the\nrapid turnover of monomer resources and for regularly varying monomer/polymer\ndiffusivities.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Mar 2012 23:46:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-12-20"}
