istic is shown to achieve a nonzero information\nacquisition rate, establishing a lower bound for the maximum achievable rate\nand error exponent. In the case of a noisy dynamic search with size-independent\nnoise, the obtained nonzero rate and error exponent are shown to be maximum.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Mar 2012 23:52:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 23 Apr 2012 19:58:23 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 11 Oct 2012 09:15:28 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 18 Dec 2013 09:47:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-12-19"}
