ion. However at high stellar temperatures the calculated\n$\\beta^{+}$-decay rates are almost half of FFN rates. On the other hand, for\nrp-process conditions, the calculated electron capture ($\\beta^{+}$-decay)\nrates are bigger than FFN rates by more than a factor 2 (1.5) and may have\ninteresting astrophysical consequences.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Mar 2012 08:21:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-03-22"}
